<subSubSection id="A486148478653A43FF60D74F86A46311" pageId="4" pageNumber="283" type="description">
<paragraph id="EC23470F78653A43FF60D74F87966007" blockId="4.[129,767,1851,1908]" box="[129,706,1883,1908]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">
E.M.FRIIS, P.R.CRANE et K.R.PEDERSEN 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="C5DB266678653A43FDC0D74F87966007" box="[545,706,1884,1908]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EC23470F78653A43FF47D79887A960D6" blockId="4.[129,765,1931,1987]" box="[166,765,1931,1955]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">P l a n t F o s s i l N a m e s R e g i s t r y N u m b e r.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EC23470F78653A43FF60D7B884EC60B7" blockId="4.[129,765,1931,1987]" box="[129,440,1963,1987]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">PFN000904 (for new genus).</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EC23470F78653A43FF47D7C887A76F40" blockId="4.[129,768,2011,2100]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">
E t y m o l o g y. In honour of Rachel Lambert Mellon (1910 â€“ 2014) for her strong engagement and support of plants and environment in 
<collectingRegion id="2E5889ED78653A43FEB5D80F84FE6F40" box="[340,426,2076,2100]" country="United States of America" name="Virginia" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Virginia</collectingRegion>
where the fossil was collected.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EC23470F78653A43FC90D08B803766C5" blockId="4.[843,1482,152,434]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">D i a g n o s i s. Flower structurally bisexual, with multiparted perianth, androecium and gynoecium. Floral receptacle conical, elongate. Perianth of about 30 tepals spirally arranged in several series. Tepals all sepaloid and free from each other, narrowly elongate with rhomboidal bases. Androecium of several free stamens, apparently spirally arranged in at least two series. Gynoecium apocarpous, of many free carpels borne on the conical receptacle; ovary superior. Large, secretory cells in all floral tissues.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EC23470F78653A43FC90D1DA86A46311" blockId="4.[843,1483,457,1125]" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">
C o m m e n t s o n t h e g e n u s. The flower of 
<taxonomicName id="2B9C3C8C78653A43FCAAD1FA868B6575" authorityName="E. M. FRIIS, P. R. CRANE et K. R. PEDERSEN" authorityYear="2020" box="[843,991,489,513]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Chloranthaceae" genus="Lambertiflora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Chloranthales" pageId="4" pageNumber="283" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DEE89B1D78653A43FCAAD1FA868B6575" box="[843,991,489,513]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Lambertiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is preserved in a pre-anthetic stage with androecium and gynoecium not fully differentiated. 
<taxonomicName id="2B9C3C8C78653A43FCAAD239868B6536" authorityName="E. M. FRIIS, P. R. CRANE et K. R. PEDERSEN" authorityYear="2020" box="[843,991,554,578]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Chloranthaceae" genus="Lambertiflora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Chloranthales" pageId="4" pageNumber="283" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DEE89B1D78653A43FCAAD239868B6536" box="[843,991,554,578]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Lambertiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from all other multiparted flowers described from the Cretaceous by its long, narrow tepals. It is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="2B9C3C8C78653A43FB74D279806665F6" authorityName="E. M. FRIIS, P. R. CRANE et K. R. PEDERSEN" authorityYear="2020" box="[1173,1330,618,642]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Chloranthaceae" genus="Mugideiriflora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Chloranthales" pageId="4" pageNumber="283" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DEE89B1D78653A43FB74D279806665F6" box="[1173,1330,618,642]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Mugideiriflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its conical receptacle that is elongated in the gynoecial zone, and its spirally arranged perianth parts, but 
<taxonomicName id="2B9C3C8C78653A43FB04D2B9802D65B6" authorityName="E. M. FRIIS, P. R. CRANE et K. R. PEDERSEN" authorityYear="2020" box="[1253,1401,682,706]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Chloranthaceae" genus="Lambertiflora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Chloranthales" pageId="4" pageNumber="283" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DEE89B1D78653A43FB04D2B9802D65B6" box="[1253,1401,682,706]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Lambertiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in having tepals of only one kind, whereas 
<taxonomicName id="2B9C3C8C78653A43FACCD2D8809E6597" authorityName="E. M. FRIIS, P. R. CRANE et K. R. PEDERSEN" authorityYear="2020" box="[1325,1482,715,739]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Chloranthaceae" genus="Mugideiriflora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Chloranthales" pageId="4" pageNumber="283" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DEE89B1D78653A43FACCD2D8809E6597" box="[1325,1482,715,739]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Mugideiriflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has differentiated tepals. 
<taxonomicName id="2B9C3C8C78653A43FB95D2F8805C6477" authorityName="E. M. FRIIS, P. R. CRANE et K. R. PEDERSEN" authorityYear="2020" box="[1140,1288,747,771]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Chloranthaceae" genus="Lambertiflora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Chloranthales" pageId="4" pageNumber="283" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DEE89B1D78653A43FB95D2F8805C6477" box="[1140,1288,747,771]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Lambertiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="2B9C3C8C78653A43FC68D31881746457" authorityName="E. M. FRIIS, P. R. CRANE et K. R. PEDERSEN" authorityYear="2020" box="[905,1056,779,803]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Chloranthaceae" genus="Atlantocarpus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Chloranthales" pageId="4" pageNumber="283" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DEE89B1D78653A43FC68D31881746457" box="[905,1056,779,803]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Atlantocarpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its much shorter receptacle and its greater number of tepals. 
<taxonomicName id="2B9C3C8C78653A43FB94D338805D6437" authorityName="E. M. FRIIS, P. R. CRANE et K. R. PEDERSEN" authorityYear="2020" box="[1141,1289,811,835]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Chloranthaceae" genus="Lambertiflora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Chloranthales" pageId="4" pageNumber="283" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DEE89B1D78653A43FB94D338805D6437" box="[1141,1289,811,835]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Lambertiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the two other multiparted flowers described previously from the Puddledock mesofossil flora, 
<emphasis id="DEE89B1D78653A43FB5FD37F801764F0" box="[1214,1347,876,900]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Melloniflora</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="2B9C3C8C78653A43FAAFD37E81AD64D7" authority="E. M. FRIIS, P. R. CRANE et K. R. PEDERSEN" authorityName="E. M. FRIIS, P. R. CRANE et K. R. PEDERSEN" authorityYear="2020" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Chloranthaceae" genus="Atlantocarpus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Chloranthales" pageId="4" pageNumber="283" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="virginiensis">
<emphasis id="DEE89B1D78653A43FAAFD37E809D64F0" box="[1358,1481,877,900]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">virginiensis</emphasis>
E.M.FRIIS, P.R.CRANE et K.R.PEDERSEN
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="2B9C3C8C78653A43FADBD39F86EF6497" authority="E. M. FRIIS, H. EKLUND, K. R. PEDERSEN et P. R. CRANE" authorityName="E. M. FRIIS, H. EKLUND, K. R. PEDERSEN et P. R. CRANE" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Calycanthaceae" genus="Virginianthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="4" pageNumber="283" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="calycanthoides">
<emphasis id="DEE89B1D78653A43FADBD39F86BF64B0" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Virginianthus calycanthoides</emphasis>
E.M.FRIIS, H. EKLUND, K.R.PEDERSEN et P.R.CRANE
</taxonomicName>
, by its conical floral receptacle that is elongated in the gynoecial zone. In 
<emphasis id="DEE89B1D78653A43FBBAD3FE80366370" box="[1115,1378,1005,1029]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">
Melloniflora 
<taxonomicName id="2B9C3C8C78653A43FB06D3FE80366370" authorityName="E. M. FRIIS, P. R. CRANE et K. R. PEDERSEN" authorityYear="2020" box="[1255,1378,1005,1028]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Chloranthaceae" genus="Atlantocarpus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Chloranthales" pageId="4" pageNumber="283" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="virginiensis">virginiensis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
the floral receptacle is flat while in 
<taxonomicName id="2B9C3C8C78653A43FB95D41E80FB6351" box="[1140,1455,1037,1061]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Calycanthaceae" genus="Virginianthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="4" pageNumber="283" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="calycanthoides">
<emphasis id="DEE89B1D78653A43FB95D41E80FB6351" box="[1140,1455,1037,1061]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="283">Virginianthus calycanthoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it forms a distinct cup. For further comparison and references, see Discussion.
</paragraph>
